<para id="eip-id1170662297385">Clearly, the point (4, 8) gives the most profit: $400.</para>
<para id="eip-id1170664960526">Therefore, we conclude that Niki should work 4 hours at Job I, and 8 hours at Job II.</para>
 </solution>
      </exercise>
</example>
      
        
     
     
      <example id="eip-id1170673685524">
      <exercise id="id1171087003889">
        <problem id="oo-id1171111606826">
          <para id="id1171087616498">A factory manufactures two types of gadgets, regular and premium. Each gadget requires the use of two operations, assembly and finishing, and there are at most 12 hours available for each operation. A regular gadget requires 1 hour of assembly and 2 hours of finishing, while a premium gadget needs 2 hours of assembly and 1 hour of finishing. Due to other restrictions, the company can make at most 7 gadgets a day. If a profit of $20 is realized for each regular gadget and $30 for a premium gadget, how many of each should be manufactured to maximize profit? </para>
        </problem>
        <solution id="oo-id1171084357636">
          <para id="id1171086147731">We choose our variables. </para>
          <para id="id1171086509476">  Let 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>The number of regular gadgets manufactured each day</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x="The number of regular gadgets manufactured each day" "." } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></para>
          <para id="id1171085379644">  and 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>The number of premium gadgets manufactured each day</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{y="The number of premium gadgets manufactured each day" "." } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></para>
          <para id="id1171113564646">The objective function is </para>
          <equation id="eip-id1170693226051">
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>20</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mtext>30</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{P="20"x+"30"y} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation>
          <para id="id1171092030428">We now write the constraints. The fourth sentence states that the company can make at most 7 gadgets a day. This translates as  </para>
          <equation id="eip-id1170670453891">
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">≤</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x+y &lt;= 7} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation>
          <para id="id1171118531613">Since the regular gadget requires one hour of assembly and the premium gadget requires two hours of assembly, and there are at most 12 hours available for this operation, we get</para>
          <equation id="eip-id1170684127313">
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mn>2y</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">≤</m:mo><m:mtext>12</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x+2y &lt;= "12"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation>
          <para id="id1171113685831">Similarly, the regular gadget requires two hours of finishing and the premium gadget one hour. Again, there are at most 12 hours available for finishing. This gives us the following constraint.</para>
          <equation id="eip-id1170671129171">
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>2x</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">≤</m:mo><m:mtext>12</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{2x+y &lt;= "12"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation>
          <para id="id1171083453595">The fact that 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{y} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can never be negative is represented by the following two constraints:</para>
          <para id="id1171085393727"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">≥</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x &gt;= 0} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, and 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">≥</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{y &gt;= 0} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para>
          <para id="id1171109877313">We have formulated the problem as follows:</para>
          <para id="id1171084644834">
            <emphasis effect="bold">Maximize</emphasis>
            <m:math>
              <m:semantics>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>P</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                          <m:mtext>20</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                          <m:mtext>30</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mstyle>
                  <m:mrow/>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{P="20"x+"30"y} {}</m:annotation>
              </m:semantics>
            </m:math>
          </para>
          <para id="id1171113954722">
            <emphasis effect="bold">Subject to:</emphasis>
            <m:math>
              <m:semantics>
                <m:mrow>
